title: open_in_internet_explorer
body:
Old browsers such as [[Internet Explorer]] 8 and earlier had a unique quirk on how they rendered images when they're highlighted. Artists at the time took advantage of that and added "subliminal" images in their art as a bonus for those that use such browsers.

h6. Explanation of how it works

The trick works because those legacy versions of Internet Explorer highlight images using a non-transparent grid pattern, which cancels out one of the two images that have been interleaved into one image using the grid pattern. It dosn't work in modern browsers because they tint images, rather than using the grid method.

Basically, the grid method works like this. Two images are put together like so:

121212121
212121212
121212121
212121212

When highlighted, the "1" image is masked by the highlight, thus this is the result:

#2#2#2#2#
2#2#2#2#2
#2#2#2#2#
2#2#2#2#2
#2#2#2#2#

and the second image can then be plainly seen.

h6. Viewing hidden images without legacy versions of Internet Explorer

Here is a method of revealing the hidden image using a layer-based image editor like Photoshop or GIMP:

* Open the image.
* Create a new black or white layer above the original image. On this new layer, attach a [i]layer mask[/i].
* Render a 1-pixel black and white checkerboard pattern as the layer mask. This effectively creates an opaque solid color layer where every other pixel is transparent.
* Nudge the checkerboard layer one pixel at a time to switch between images.

Consult the documentation or Google instructions on how to use layer masks and render checkerboards in your image editor.

title: keyarga_(kaiyari)
body:
The male protagonist of the series [[Kaifuku Jutsushi no Yarinaoshi ~Sokushi Mahou to Skill Copy no Chouetsu Heal~]].  The Hero of Recovery, Keyarga's real name is Keyaru, but took on an alias after becoming a wanted man by the Gioral Kingdom.  He has [[brown hair]] and [[brown eyes|eyes]], and possesses magic sight in his right eye that [[glowing eye|glows]] green when in use.  He seeks the destruction of the Gioral Kingdom and revenge against Gioral's Hero Party members who raped, abused, and used him in the timeline before he rewound time.

His name and aliases are derived from the naming of healing spells from [[Final Fantasy]].  Cure (Kearu) -> Keyaru, Curaga (Kearuga) -> Keyarga, Cura (Kearura) -> Keyarura.

body:
[b]XM-X1 (F97) Crossbone Gundam X-1[/b]
A custom, pirate stylised mobile suit developed for the Crossbone Vanguard to be used in the Jupiter Sphere. To account for the extreme gravitational pull of Jupiter, it was given a revolutionary X-shaped thruster arrangement that kept the power high and the weight low, granting it fantastic mobility in Jupiter's orbit - and had the additional of causing the unit to be borderline out of control in the weaker gravity of Earth's sphere. It was primarily piloted by [[Kincade Nau]].

title: hata-tan_(rui_(hershe))
body:
A dark, depressed, "emo" variant of [[Himekaidou Hatate]] of [[Touhou]]. Created and popularized by [[rui (hershe)]], alongside similarly dark variations of [[Shameimaru Aya]], [[Inubashiri Momiji]], [[Murasa Minamitsu]], and [[Kawashiro Nitori]].

In his story, Hatate is a schoolgirl in love with Aya. However, Aya verbally and physically bullies Hatate, who tolerates and may even be masochistically turned on by the abuse. Momiji is sympathetic to her, but because she's a lackey to Aya, she doesn't involve herself. Nitori appears to be Hatate's online friend. Murasa is Aya's rival.

[[Black hair]] is a common Hata-tan trait, but isn't required. Images may also include some combination of [[bags_under_eyes|bags under the eyes]], [[bullying]], [[scar|scars]], marks around the neck from choking, a [[hikikomori]] or obsessive, [[yandere]] character, often with Aya as the focus, or identification as Hata-tan by the artist.

title: oyster_pail
body:
A folded [[takeout container]] often used in American Chinese takeout cuisine.  

Made using folded waxed or plastic coated paper, oyster pails were originally created as a cheap disposable container to hold fresh shucked oysters. With the rise in popularity of takeout of American Chinese food, they became widely used by American Chinese restaurants for their cheap and leak resistant design.  Given this common use by Chinese restaurants, they became commonly known as [i]Chinese food boxes[/i] or [i]Chinese takeout containers[/i].

A main character from [[Durarara!!]].

A [[Dullahan]], she left her native Ireland and came to Japan in search of her lost [[disembodied head|head]].  She rides a [[motorcycle]] possessed by her ghost horse, and in public wears a full-body black [[bikesuit]] and bright yellow cat-eared [[motorcycle helmet]] to conceal her fae nature.  Due to her lack of a head she [[mute|cannot speak]] and instead uses a smartphone-like text entry device to communicate. (In the anime adaptation, she is voiced in certain scenes as a form of dramatic license).

Celty's neck ends at a black surface which continually emits black smoke. Celty can freely manipulate this smoke, forming it into various shapes and solidifying it. Her bikesuit is in fact made of it, which allows her to transform it into different clothing.

[spoilers]Celty's head, which in fanart can be depicted reattached, has short, reddish-brown hair and blue-green eyes.[/spoilers]

title: chiffon_cake
body: A very light [[cake]] made with vegetable oil, eggs, sugar, flour, baking powder, and flavoring. It is unique in that it uses vegetable oil rather than traditional fats such as butter or shortening that are solid at room temperature. This makes it difficult to beat air directly into the batter. Therefore, chiffon cakes (as well as angel cakes and other foam cakes) achieve fluffiness by beating the egg whites separately until stiff and then folding them into the cake batter before baking. Its aeration depends on the quality of the [[meringue]] and the chemical leavening agent. Chiffon cake combines the methods of [[sponge cake]] and traditional cake. It includes baking powder and vegetable oil, but the eggs are separated and the egg whites are beaten and then folded into the batter, creating a rich flavor like an oil cake, but with a lighter texture, more like a sponge cake. It can be baked in a tube pan, or layered with filling and frosting. In the original recipe, the cake tin is not lined or greased, which allows the cake batter to stick to the sides of the pan, allowing the cake to rise better, and also provides support to keep the bubbles stable while the cake cools upside down.

title: kunreishiki
body:
"Kunrei-shiki romanization":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kunrei-shiki_romanization is the system for romanizing Japanese characters officially promoted by the Japanese government and taught in schools. It's intended to maintain consistency with the way kana are written without being a literal representation of the way the syllables actually sound (e.g., "sa", "si" and "sya" instead of "sa", "shi" and "sha".) For this reason, many English speakers find that it looks strange and prefer to use "Hepburn romanization":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hepburn_romanization, which is also used in the spelling of tags throughout Danbooru.

See also: [[Romaji text]].

title: golf_course
body: A golf course is a venue where the game of golf is played. It consists of a series of holes, each consisting of a teeing ground, a fairway, grass and other hazards, and a green with a flagstick and hole. A standard round of golf consists of eighteen holes. Most courses contain eighteen holes; some courses share fairways or greens, and there is a subset with nine holes that are played twice per round. Par 3 courses consist of nine or eighteen holes, all of which have a par of three.

title: speedpaint
body:
An artistic technique in which the artist completes the work in a limited amount of time. The time can vary and is usually set from a few minutes to a few hours. Unlike sketching, speed painting can be considered "finished" when the time limit is reached. Speed painting is particularly common among digital media artists because the digital painting medium allows the work to circumvent the drying time of traditional media. Digital media artists primarily use speed painting to practice working quickly and efficiently. Speed painting techniques are also often used in conceptual art, especially in the early stages of production when the polish of a single image is more important than the clear basic presentation of many candidate concepts.

Traditional media artists also use time-limited work as a challenge to technique and as an exercise in not overthinking the work. Both digital and traditional quick-draw works are considered by artists to be excellent demonstrations of the painter's subjective skills, as time constraints require efficient rendering of form and detail, as well as a deep understanding of the chosen medium, to capture a complete, intense image with little time left to notice and correct errors. Danny Dent is recognized by many as the pioneer of speed painting in the United States, having introduced speed painting in live performance in 1981.

[expand=Table of Contents]
* 1. "Any format":#dtext-any
** 1.01 "Page":#dtext-page
** 1.02 "Limit":#dtext-limit
** 1.03 "Search":#dtext-search
* 02. "XML/JSON":#dtext-xml-json
** 2.01 "Only":#dtext-only
* 3. "See also":#dtext-see-also
[/expand]

With the URLs used for navigation around the site, there are several common URL parameters which can be used.

h4#any. Any format

The parameters can be used on any format, which includes HTML, ATOM, XML, and JSON.

h5#page. [u]Page[/u]

The method by which different sections of the database can be viewed. This parameter can be either numeric or sequential. For both the name of the parameter key is "page".

h6#numeric. |Numeric|

Used on the index views, it determines the starting position of the records shown. It is an integer that must be greater than zero. Any ordering parameter available for the various records may be used.

* [b]Example:[/b] [code]page=1[/code]

The following is the equation used for the record starting position.

[code]
(page - 1) * limit
[/code]

Where limit is the number of records shown per page, as explained later below.

h6#sequential. |Sequential|

Uses the record ID numbers instead to determine the starting or ending positions for the records. It is an integer that is prefaced with an "a" or "b". When used, the order of the records is forced as ID descending, regardless of any ordering parameter

* [b]Example:[/b] [code]page=a12345[/code]

When prefaced by "a", the integer marks the ending position where records must be above that ID.

When prefaced by "b", it marks the starting position where records must be below that ID.

h5#limit. [u]Limit[/u]

The number of results to show per page. It is an integer that must be greater than zero. The name of the parameter key is "limit".

* [b]Example:[/b] [code]limit=100[/code]

h5#search. [u]Search[/u]

All search parameters use URL hash format ([[Help:Hash syntax]]) where "search" is the base object.

[b]Example:[/b] [code]search[PARAMETER]=VALUE[/code]

h6#custom-order. |Custom order|

Sets the order of the results by the order of the values requested.

* [code]search[order]=custom[/code]
* [code]search[id]=2,3,1,4[/code]

The above would return items with ID's of 2, 3, 1, 4 in that order.

Both parameters must be present to perform this type of search. Only the comma-separated version of the ID parameter is supported.

h4#xml-json. XML/JSON

These parameters are only available with the XML and JSON formats.

h5#only. [u]Only[/u]

Determines the list of attributes that will be returned. The attributes must be comma separated, though can be in any order. The name of the parameter key is "only".

* [b]Example:[/b] [code]only=id,name,created_at[/code]

[code]
[
  {
    "id": 200403,
    "created_at": "2020-03-15T17:16:15.772Z",
    "name": "spica_s"
  }
]
[/code]

h6#associated-attributes. |Associated attributes|

The only parameter may also be used to included other records that have associations with that particular record type. To include the record, the name of the association must be added to the comma separated list like any other attribute. 

* [b]Example:[/b] [code]only=tag[/code]

When an associated attribute is included, the entire record of that attribute is added to the hash of the record returned.

[code]
[
  {
    "tag": {
      "id": 1560500,
      "name": "spica_s",
      "post_count": 1,
      "category": 1,
      "created_at": "2020-03-15T17:16:15.771Z",
      "updated_at": "2020-03-15T17:16:15.771Z",
      "is_locked": false
    }
  }
]
[/code]

h6#nested-only. |Nested only|

The only parameter can be further specified onto the associated attributes. This is indicated by the use of square brackets "[ ]", where the square brackets are next to the name of the associated attribute. The only parameters are a comma separated list inside the square brackets.

* [b]Example:[/b] [code]only=tag_alias[consequent_name,status,forum_topic_id][/code]

[code]
[
  {
    "tag_alias": {
      "consequent_name": "claire_stanfield",
      "status": "active",
      "forum_topic_id": null
    }
  }
]
[/code]

h6#nested-attributes. |Nested attributes|

Associated attributes can be further specified on the associated attributes. Like above, the name of these associated attributes must be included in the square brackets.

* [b]Example:[/b] [code]only=post[comments][/code]

[code]
[
  {
    "post": {
      "comments": [
        {
          "id": 1988814,
          "created_at": "2020-03-13T20:28:53.565Z",
          "post_id": 3770941,
          "creator_id": 561532,
          "body": "Bomp",
          "score": 0,
          "updated_at": "2020-03-13T20:28:53.565Z",
          "updater_id": 561532,
          "do_not_bump_post": false,
          "is_deleted": false,
          "is_sticky": false
        }
      ]
    }
  }
]
[/code]

h6#recursion. |Recursion|

The only and associated attributes can be chained through all available attributes on all available models.

* [b]Example:[/b] [code]only=artist[urls[url]][/code]

[code]
[
  {
    "artist": {
      "urls": [
        {
          "url": "https://shirokurokun.tumblr.com"
        },
        {
          "url": "https://twitter.com/pancakehotmot"
        }
      ]
    }
  }
]
[/code]

One imposed limitation on this is that a particular record type may only be included twice down any particular attribute chain.

* [b]Example:[/b] notes --> post --> notes -X> post

This is to prevent endless recursion.

h4#see-also. See also

* [[Help:API]]

title: help:enum_syntax
body:
When searching by enums, the following variation in search parameters may be used. For all of the following, substitute [b]NAME[/b] for the name of the enum attribute.

h5. NAME

Searches for enum values by name instead of by integer. Multiple enum values can be passed separated by spaces.

h5. NAME_not

Excludes enum values by name instead of by integer. Multiple enum values can be excluded separated by spaces.

h5. NAME_id

All variations of this parameter are handled the same as numeric attributes ([[Help:Number syntax]]).

h4. See also

* [[Help:Number syntax]]
* [[Help:API]]

title: seiken_densetsu_3
body:
Third game in the [[Seiken Densetsu]] series, originally for the [[Super Famicom]] / [[Super Nintendo]].

Unlike [[Seiken Densetsu 2]] (Secret of Mana), Seiken Densetsu 3 was not available outside of Japan at release, though it was eventually released as part of the Collection of Mana as [b]Trials of Mana[/b]. An English fan translation patch was made available in 2000. 

A remake was officially announced June 11, 2019, bringing the game to the West, the same day Collection of Mana was released outside Japan. The remake itself officially released April 24, 2020.

The game features 6 playable characters, from which the player chooses a team of three. The story changes depending on which characters are chosen.

* [[Riesz]] (Lise in fan translation)

title: planet_glorie
body:
A fictional [[alien]] [[planet]] from the [[Choujikuu Kidan Southern Cross]] [[mecha]] anime series from the 1980s.

[b]Planet Glorie[/b] is an Earth-type planet with different environments and several types of weather. While most of the surface is covered with deserts and arid mountainous zones, it also has small oceans, some jungles, temperate forests and cold polar zones.

For several decades large populations of humans have colonized and terraformed the planet to make it their home.

The army of the Southern Cross is in charge of protecting its numerous human colonies.

The transformation into this form happens when the battleship's core is injected with a great quantity of [[Spiral Power]] by the [[Arc Gurren-Lagann]].

It is the third largest mecha in the series, being almost as large in size as the [[Moon]].

The two drills on its shoulders can be detached and combined to form a single drill, then used to perform the [i]Chouginga Giga Drill Breaker[/i] attack. According to Lordgenome, its power equals that of a sub-universe.

title: kikou_kantai_dairugger_xv
body:
[i][b]Kikou Kantai Dairugger XV[/b][/i] (fifteen) ([i][b]Armored Fleet Dairugger XV[/b][/i]) was a [[science fiction]] [[super robot]] [[mecha]] anime and space opera series that aired in Japan from 1982 to 1983. 

It is also referred to as [b][i]Dairugger 15[/i][/b], [b][i]Dairugger XV[/i][/b], [b][i]Armored Armada Dairugger XV[/i][/b], [b][i]Armored Squadron Dairugger XV[/i][/b], or [b][i]Machine Platoon Dairugger[/i][/b].

In the far future planet Earth is in a time of peace and prosperity. The president of the Terran League launches a mission to explore [[milky_way|our galaxy]] and build a complete map of the stars. The Rugger Team is an exploration, planetary survey, and defensive fleet that is assigned such mission. However, soon after commencing their voyage, the Rugger Team and their flagship, the Rugger Guard, are attacked by the powerful, evil and tyrannical Galveston Empire. [[dairugger_xv_(mecha)|Dairugger XV]], the legendary super robot, must defend the Rugger Guard and its fleet as they attempt to continue their mission.

In the United States, the original series was heavily edited to become part of the Voltron series. Dairugger is known in the U.S. as [b][i]Voltron - Vehicle Team[/i][/b] or [b][i]Voltron of the Near Universe[/i][/b].

For [i]Dairugger[/i] elements only present in [i]Voltron[/i] continuity, use the [[Voltron (series)]] tag.

h4. See also

title: dino_riders
body:
[b]Dino Riders[/b] is an American [[Science fiction]] cartoon television series that first aired in 1988. Dino Riders was primarily made as a promotion campaign to launch a "Tyco" [[dinosaur]] themed toy line. Only fourteen episodes were produced, three of which were produced on VHS for the United States. It aired in the U.S. as part of the [[Marvel]] Action Universe.

The series focuses on the battle between the good [[Valorian]]s and the evil [[Rulon]]s on a prehistoric Earth. The Valorians were a super human race, whilst the Rulons were a mixture of humanoid [[mutant]] creatures, both of which came from the future, however ended up transported back in time to the age of Dinosaurs. Once on Earth, the Valorians befriended the dinosaurs whilst the Rulons brainwashed them.

h4. External links

title: elysium_(movie)
body:
[b]Elysium[/b] is a 2013 American [[science fiction]], [[cyberpunk]] action-thriller film written, co-produced and directed by Neill Blomkamp and starring Matt Damon, Jodie Foster, Sharlto Copley, Alice Braga and Diego Luna. It was released on August 9, 2013.

The film takes place in the year 2154, when two classes of people exist: the very wealthy, who live on a luxurious [[space station]] called "Elysium" and the poor, who live on an overpopulated and contaminated Earth. 

The movie explores political and sociological themes such as immigration, overpopulation, transhumanism, health care, exploitation and class issues.

title: oh!_mouretsu
body:
From the English "Panchira wiki":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Panchira#Origins

"In 1969, the Japanese oil company Maruzen Sekiyuu released a television commercial featuring Rooza Ogawa in a short mini-skirt that gets blown up by the wind with her forming her lips into an 'O' in surprise. This led to children imitating her line "Oh Mouretsu" (Oh！モーレツ, too much, radical), and a fad for skaato-mekuri (スカート捲り flipping up of a girl's skirt).[11] Ogawa subsequently appeared in a TV show Oh Sore Miyo (Oh! それ見よ, literally "look at that," but actually a pun on 'O Sole Mio,' a neapolitan song 'my sunshine') that again featured scenes of her mini-skirt blowing up."

"The famous pose":http://jcmndful.tumblr.com/image/102132826135

"The 30-second spot":https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=b5dgWaRsjI4

Related: [[ogawa_rooza]]

"Wait for me Louisa."
That was Graham, Louisa's childhood friends and lover last word to her before he departed on a journey to defeat the Demon King. However Louisa has no intention to wait. The truth is, Louisa remember three of her previous lives. In all of them, she was the heroes childhood friend and lover, and every single time, the hero never came back from his journey and married another woman.
So this time, she will not wait for him and left the village to find her own happiness.

title: planisphere
body: A [b]planisphere[/b], also known as a [b]star wheel[/b], is an analog computer used to determine the positions of stars in the night sky at any given date or time.  It consists of two independently rotating discs, one containing a star chart calibrated for use at a particular latitude, the other a moving window that enables the user to display only the portion of the chart that corresponds to the visible sky at the time and date desired.  This is used by (mostly amateur) astronomers to orient themselves and get a sense of what to expect and where to look for it during observations.

title: fsb
body: The Federal Security Service of the Russian Federation (FSB RF; Russian: Федеральная служба безопасности Российской Федерации (ФСБ), tr. Federal'naya sluzhba bezopasnosti Rossiyskoy Federatsii, IPA: [fʲɪdʲɪˈralʲnəjə ˈsluʐbə bʲɪzɐˈpasnəstʲɪ rɐˈsʲijskəj fʲɪdʲɪˈratsɨjɪ]) is the principal security agency of Russia and the main successor agency to the USSR's KGB ('Committee for State Securityʼ). Its main responsibilities are within the country and include counter-intelligence, internal and border security, counter-terrorism, and surveillance as well as investigating some other types of grave crimes and federal law violations. It is headquartered in Lubyanka Square, Moscow's center, in the main building of the former KGB. According to the 1995 Federal Law "On the Federal Security Service", direction of the FSB is executed by the president of Russia, who appoints the Director of the FSB.

title: hamburglar
body:
* Hamburglar - The Hamburglar was a pint-sized thief who first appeared in March 1971 and one of the first villains on the commercials. He is dressed in a black-and-white hooped shirt and pants, a red cape, a wide-brimmed hat, and red gloves; hamburgers are his primary target. The character, like Grimace, started out as a villain, only he was older, had a long nose, and gray hair. He was revised in the mid-80s: his look changed from a trollish old man to a red-headed child, and his unintelligible muttering became the familiar "robble robble." 
*Hamburglar was later retired. In the 2000s, he was temporarily revived for an ad campaign for generic burgers instead of Happy Meals. In "The Wacky Adventures of Ronald McDonald," he takes on a new sporty appearance wearing green goggles, a leather jacket, striped shirt, shorts and sneakers. 
*He loves playing tricks on his friends and still loves burgers.

The [b]harmonica[/b], also [b]French harp[/b], [b]blues harp[/b], and [b]mouth organ[/b], is a free reed wind [[instrument]] used worldwide in nearly every musical genre, notably in blues, American folk music, jazz, country, and rock and roll. There are many types of harmonica, including diatonic, chromatic, tremolo, octave, orchestral, and bass versions. A harmonica is played by using the mouth (lips and/or tongue) to direct air into and out of one or more holes along a mouthpiece.

title: serbia_strong
body:
Also known as "[b]Remove Kebab[/b]" or "[b]God Is a Serb [and He Will Protect Us][/b]", and originally as "[b]Karadžić, Lead Your Serbs[/b]".

A propagandistic music video showing four soldiers, three of whom play musical instruments. The most common version of the music video available online includes edited-in footage of Radovan Karadžić drinking water at the Hague during his 2008 trial, likely to parody the original producer's intent. The accordionist stands out because of his unmoving and emotionless face as he plays the instrument. 

The Serbian politician the song was sung to as a tribute, Radovan Karadžić, the accordionist, Novislav Đajić and the assumed producer, Nikola Jorgić, were all convicted as war criminals (for genocide, among other charges) a couple of years after the musical video was produced.
